subSubSection.paragraph:
DIAGNOSIS: This species, known only from macropterous specimens, is distinguished from other species by the small size; uniformly yellow coloration (
figs. 32, 33
), often with a faint orange tinge; silvery sericeous pubescence on the dorsum; and the pallid tibial spines lacking spots at the bases.

