subSubSection.paragraph:
DIAGNOSIS: This species is recognized by the overall gray to grayish-green coloration (
figs. 34, 35
), with numerous fuscous spots on the dorsum, legs, and antennae; and the long rostrum that extends to near the base of the genital capsule. Males (
fig. 34
) are always macropterous, whereas females are known from both macropterous and subbrachypterous (
fig. 35
) or short-winged individuals with abbreviated hemelytral membranes.
